{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"764dc6ff-9ed8-4ead-83e5-b7c279a9f569","content":"This is a well-known MTP behavioral difference. **Exit code 8** means \"no tests were discovered.\" VSTest returned 0 in this case; MTP treats it as an error to catch misconfiguration.\n\nSince your assembly legitimately has zero tests in some configurations, you have two options:\n\n### Option 1 — Ignore exit code 8 at the project level (recommended)\n\nAdd this MSBuild property to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<TestingPlatformExitCodeOnNoTests>0</TestingPlatformExitCodeOnNoTests>\n```\n\nThis tells MTP to return 0 instead of 8 when no tests are found.\n\n### Option 2 — Set it via environment variable in CI\n\n```bash\nset TESTINGPLATFORM_EXITCODE_IGNORE=8\n```\n\nThis works across all test projects without editing each `.csproj`.\n\n---\n\nLet me apply Option 1 to your project:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_017VvemxpmeFMZTcgUjQ1oQ1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-001834b9a41c48c5a2dfc16274c4bf77/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n    <TestingPlatformExitCodeOnNoTests>0</TestingPlatformExitCodeOnNoTests>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-001834b9a41c48c5a2dfc16274c4bf77/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"108e557d-346f-452f-9e79-ed82967f2b48","outputTokens":454,"requestId":"A029:14C0A3:1769FB1:1A91C86:69FE8778"},"id":"dca7c83e-5255-43a0-9b0b-fd2ed43388eb","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:01:52.644Z","parentId":"c3844a4b-8c98-4c09-ada1-5c71d02a2b7f"}
